					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6034487#post-3839696</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6034487/scp-3523#post-3839696</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 18 Jun 2018 05:27:56 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Zinitrad</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2553506</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>29% of all clay world wide is an awful lot to have be affected by this, don't you think? Unless you're going for the 'apocalyptic containment failure' sort of setting some scps go for, this one really pushes the limit of phenomenon that are hard to believe they're suppressed.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
